Write a very short story using the following words. Every time a word is used, insert the meaning of the Chinese word after the word. The format is as follows: English word [Chinese meaning]."
declaration [ˌdɛkləˈreɪʃən]【声明，宣言】
allegiance [əˈlidʒəns]【忠诚，效忠】
defence [dɪˈfɛns]【防御，保卫】
allegiance [əˈlidʒəns]【忠诚，效忠】
period [ˈpɪəriəd]【时期，时代】
colony [ˈkɒləni]【殖民地，群体】
religion [rɪˈlɪdʒən]【宗教】
ancestor [ˈænsɛstə]【祖先，先祖】
pledge [plɛdʒ]【誓言，保证】
cardinal [ˈkɑːdɪnl]【红衣主教，基本的，主要的】
dedicate [ˈdɛdɪkeɪt]【奉献，致力于】
courage [ˈkʌrɪdʒ]【勇气，胆量】
executive [ɪɡˈzɛkjʊtɪv]【行政的，执行的】
memorial [mɪˈmɔːrɪəl]【纪念碑，纪念馆】
envelope [ˈɛnvələʊp]【信封，封套】
collection [kəˈlɛkʃən]【收藏，收集】
festival [ˈfɛstɪvl]【节日，庆典】
constitution [ˌkɑːnstɪˈtuːʃən]【宪法，章程】
"

In the colonial [殖民地] period [时期], the leaders of the new land made a declaration [声明] of independence from their ancestors' [祖先] country. 
They pledged [誓言] their allegiance [忠诚] to the cardinal [基本的，主要的] principles of freedom and defence [保卫].
With courage [勇气], they dedicated [奉献] themselves to building a new executive [行政的，执行的] system based on the constitution [宪法]. 
Today, we celebrate the festival [节日] that honors their memorial [纪念碑，纪念馆] and the collection [收藏，收集] of artifacts from that time, 
carefully preserved in an envelope [信封，封套].

在殖民地时期，这片新土地的领袖们向祖先国宣布了独立的声明。
他们誓言效忠于自由和保卫的基本原则。他们勇气十足，致力于建立一个基于宪法的新行政体系。
今天，我们庆祝纪念碑并收藏那个时代的文物。这些文物被仔细地保存在信封中，我们为此庆祝这个节日。


During the colonial period, the leaders of the new country made a declaration of independence from the land of their ancestors.
在殖民地时期，这片新土地的领袖们向祖先国宣布了独立的声明。
They pledged  their allegiance to the cardinal principles of freedom and defence.
他们誓言效忠于自由和保卫的基本原则。
With courage, they dedicated themselves to building a new executive system based on the constitution. 
他们勇气十足，致力于建立一个基于宪法的新行政体系。
Today, we celebrate the festival that honors their memorial and the collection of artifacts from that time, 
carefully preserved in an envelope .
今天，我们庆祝纪念碑并收藏那个时代的文物。这些文物被仔细地保存在信封中，我们为此庆祝这个节日。


Write a very short story using the following words. "
environment [ɪnˈvaɪrənmənt]【环境】
avoid [əˈvɔɪd]【避免，防止】
contemporary [kənˈtɛmpərɛri]【当代的，现代的】
perception [pərˈsɛpʃən]【感知，知觉】
pattern [ˈpætərn]【模式，图案】
deposit [dɪˈpɒzɪt]【存款，押金】
adventure [ədˈvɛntʃər]【冒险，探险】
conservation [ˌkɒnsəˈveɪʃən]【保护，保存】
diversity [daɪˈvɜːsɪti]【多样性，差异性】
aid [eɪd]【帮助，援助】
depend [dɪˈpɛnd]【依赖，依靠】
prevent [prɪˈvɛnt]【预防，阻止】
budget [ˈbʌdʒɪt]【预算，财政】
principle [ˈprɪnsəpl]【原则，原理】
pattern [ˈpætərn]【模式，图案】
artifact [ˈɑːtɪfækt]【人工制品，文物】
diversity [daɪˈvɜrsəti]【多样性，差异】
conservation [ˌkɑːnsərˈveɪʃən]【保护，保存】
deposit [dɪˈpɑːzɪt]【存款，押金】
adventure [ədˈvɛntʃər]【冒险，探险】
disturb [dɪˈstɜːrb]【打扰，干扰】
quarrel [ˈkwɔːrəl]【争吵，争端】
perception [pərˈsɛpʃən]【感知，认知】
"

John was a contemporary conservationist who spent most of his time in nature, 
studying the environment and the diverse patterns it presented.
约翰是一位当代保护主义者，他把大部分时间花在自然界，
研究环境和它所呈现的各种模式。
He believed that aid could only come from understanding and preventing the disturbance of natural principles. 
他认为，援助只能来自于对自然原则的理解和防止干扰。
On one of his adventures, he stumbled upon an artifact that, to his perception, belonged to an ancient civilization.
在一次冒险中，他偶然发现了一件文物，在他看来，这件文物属于一个古老的文明。
Despite his excitement, he knew he had to deposit the artifact with the proper authorities to ensure its conservation. 
尽管他很兴奋，但他知道他必须将该文物存放在适当的机构，以确保其保存。
Later, as he was working on his budget for his next research project,
he couldn't help but quarrel with his colleague about the importance of perception in understanding the environment.
后来，当他为他的下一个研究项目制定预算时，他忍不住与他的同事就感知对理解环境的重要性发生争吵。
They agreed to disagree, but John knew that his principle of relying on observation and data would continue to guide him in his work.
他们同意持不同意见，但约翰知道，他依靠观察和数据的原则将继续指导他的工作。

Sarah was a lover of adventure and had always dreamed of exploring the diverse patterns of the contemporary environment. 
However, her perception of the world was shattered when she realized the devastating effects of human activity on the environment.
She decided to avoid contributing to the problem and make conservation a principle in her life.

She started to budget her expenses and make deposits in eco-friendly products. 
She also became an advocate for conservation and started to aid in projects that aimed to prevent the destruction of the environment.
Her actions made her depend less on material things and appreciate the beauty of nature.

One day, while on an adventure in the woods, she stumbled upon an artifact that had been buried for centuries. 
She marveled at its beauty and recognized the importance of preserving history as well as the environment. 
From that day on, Sarah made it her mission to protect the environment and artifacts alike, 
and to never let the quarrels of humans disturb the delicate balance of nature.
















